#. Tag: title
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining Windows"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:566
#, no-c-format
msgid "Several areas of the module allow you to define a list of windows. They all use the same interface, which contains the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:572
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comment:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:573
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is merely an informational text box you can use to explain what the trigger applies to or save other useful information. It is not actually used by the system for anything."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:579
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window List"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "Beneath the <guilabel>Comment</guilabel> box on the left is the list of all window definitions currently present in the trigger. Simply click on one to perform an operation on it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:586
#, no-c-format
msgid "Edit..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:589
#, no-c-format
msgid "Press this button to modify the currently selected window definition. A new window is opened that allows you to edit it. This window contains the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window Data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:599
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is where you describe the window the trigger should apply to."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid "At the top, there is a <guilabel>Comment:</guilabel> field, which is informational just like the one in the main <guilabel>Trigger</guilabel> tab."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:604
#, no-c-format
msgid "Three window characteristics are available:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Window title:</guilabel> - The title that appears at the top of the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:611
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Window class:</guilabel> - Usually the name of the application."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Window role:</guilabel> - Usually the name of the &Qt; class that makes up the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each window characteristic provides a drop-down box, and a text box below it. Enter the value you wish to test windows for in the text box. From the drop-down box, select which kind of test you wish to apply. You can use <guilabel>Is</guilabel> to require an exact match, <guilabel>Contains</guilabel> to require that the text entered be somewhere inside the full value, or <guilabel>Matches Regular Expression</guilabel> to use a regular expression to define the match. You may also perform the inverse of all these operations. Select <guilabel>Is Not Important</guilabel> if you do not wish for that particular characteristic to be examined."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:629
#, no-c-format
msgid "The easiest way to fill in this information is to open the desired window, then click the <guibutton>Autodetect</guibutton> button at the bottom of this section, and finally click on the desired trigger window. All three window characteristics will be populated with the information from that window, and you can then adjust the settings as necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:639
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window Types"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid "This lets you restrict the match to a particular type of window. The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:647
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Normal</guilabel> - A regular application window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:650
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Desktop</guilabel> - The main desktop is actually a special window all its own."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Dialog</guilabel> - A small window that is part of a normal application, such as a message box or a configuration screen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Dock</guilabel> - A small window that can be attached or detached from a main application window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:672
#, no-c-format
msgid "New..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:673
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new window definition. This opens the edit dialog described above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:678
#, no-c-format
msgid "Duplicate..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:679
#, no-c-format
msgid "This creates a new window definition with the exact same specifications as the currently selected window definition. It will open the edit dialog described above so you may make further changes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> stable5
#: index.docbook:686
#, no-c-format
msgid "Removes the currently selected window definition."
msgstr ""

